Zm_Greenbriar
===========================
This is version beta 5 of Zm_Greenbriar, a new zombie map that I created solely for the purpose of having an apocalyptic experience unlike any other.

The map includes the following in the current stage:

-- Intricate Player Spawns and Multilevel Layout

-- Optimization, applied nodraw to outside surfaces

-- Dynamic and light_spot lighting, with variable lightmap edits

-- Custom music and ambience

-- Steam, flickering lights, environmental scares

-- **Custom made random weapon boxes like in Nazi Zombies**, including one for rifles, sub-machine guns, and pistols, all in balanced locations; boxes can be used every 30 seconds and emit one of 4 random guns of their sub-class.
  
-- Custom made healing station in which players can gain up to 80 health every 30 seconds.  

-- Balanced system of gameplay such that the advantages of both zombies and humans are relatively even.  

-- Optimized and created for Zombie: Riot! Mod as well:

Zriot Mod: [ http://forums.alliedmods.net/showthread.php?p=647040 ]

Further edits will be made in the near future!  **Make sure to report all errors**, as this map is not perfect.  All criticism is welcome!  _Enjoy!_

-The Fool, May 2011

Basically, this is going to be a back to basics zombie mod map, With roots from lila pan!c, Omi_facility, ocx ORLY, Atix day, and a few others.


Everything that was a big "hit" in these maps will be re-created in my own vision inside this one.

What to expect.

- Gun room (who doesnt like gun rooms? srsly..)
- Lots of couches and vending machines
- classic barricade room
- cargo containers
- boxes
- camp spots
- Hidden areas, secrete rooms
- Fully optimized

What NOT to expect

- Vents
- Pipes
- Insanely cheap spots
- Escape version of this map
- Custom texture (i want this to be a small file size map for EZ-DL)




The general idea was to re-create a map after what zombie mod used to be, back before 2.0, before cars and trucks, escape maps, and aliens.

This map has some light and has been known to show low fps on some slower computers.  My computer, which i consider to be average never dipped below 40fps and usually stayed around 60-70 fps. This has been an off and on project. I finally had the urge to finish this the other day, and so I did. This is the final version of mansion_twilight. Players now start outside on the streets. Shoot the padlock to gain access to the maze and find your way to the mansion before you become a zombie.

THINGS I HAVE ADDED/CHANGED:
Mausoleum/Church building.
Sewer system.
New player start.
Walls around the map.
Rain/Storm noises (Courtesy of Robtronic).
New room to the left of the mansion.
updated the attic.
All doors open backwards to allow barricade creation.
The light environment is a dim blue to give it that nighttime glow.
Some new texturing around the map.

This map was originally made by ThePredator2 and then Ggodd2 and I figured we could rescue a great map. The original map was 5-15 fps. We brought it out of the ground to a 50-100 fps. We re textured the whole map to fit it and the lighting was brightened. ThePredator2 had a back of the house already made in his zombie_mansion_atnight_beta3 map, but never had it so you could access it. There are 5 ways to get back there and it looks pretty good. In this version everyone starts in the maze and runs for their lives to get to the mansion. The gates are locked so SHOOT THEM OPEN!!! :) Well I hope you all enjoy what ggodd and i took a good 3weeks to fix and revamp. This map will be featured on the -=GHS=- Server. Hope to see you there! P.S. There will be a v2 to fix some minor glitches. P.S.S. You can find v2 Here.
